name: Stephen Adebola
summary:
Experienced hands-on Architect offering strategic solutions and capability development. With experience, expertise, and a deep understanding of the financial, government and startup sectors. My main objective has always been to deliver real solutions that achieve impactful results. Focused on Integrating GenAI applications, automations, alignment, and guardrails while extending current enterprise data pipelines for RAG (Retrieval Augmentation & Generation) by embeddings the data in vector DBs & also connecting to existing API capabilities.
Skills:
•	Architecture TOGAF, Data, ML, AI, Cloud, Applications, IoT, Blockchain, Security, HLD/LLD
•	Domains Government, Policing, Insurance (Underwriting, Broker, Lloyds), Startups
•	General Strategy, Stakeholder Management, Procurement, Workshops & Mentoring
•	Patterns EDA, Event sourcing, CQRS, REST/GraphQL API’s, RAG
•	Cloud AWS, GCP, Azure, Colab, Hugging Face, RunPod, Railway & Render
•	Integration M&A, Multi Cloud, SaaS, PaaS, API, Messaging, Data, Events
•	DevSecFinOps IaC, PaaS, CI/CD, SEIM, Monitoring (Observability & Control) Automation.
•	Containerization Docker & AKS (Azure Kubernetes Service), EKS, CloudRun
•	Application SDLC, Web, Mobile, Assistants, Agile Methodologies, Migration, Integration
•	Data Migration, ETL, ELT, MLFlow, Pipelines, DWH, Lakehouse, Curation, DG & DG
•	CRM Salesforce, HubSpot
•	Databases SQL, NOSQL, Datalake, Lakehouse, Graph & Vector DBs, Databricks, Snowflake
•	IAM (Identity and Access Management), Active Directory, B2B, B2C, RBAC & ABAC
•	Security Zero Trust, Encryption (In Motion, At Rest), PIM/PAM
•	Programming Python, JavaScript, Java, Terraform, CLI
•	AI Assistants Azure Promptflow, Duet, Co-Pilot, Databricks Assistant, OpenAI Assistant API
•	GenAI Agents, Frameworks, Alignment, Guardrails, Prompt Engineering & Fine-tuning LLMs
•	Models GPT-3.5-Turbo, GPT-4-Turbo, GPT-4-Vision, Text-Davinci-003, TTS, Wisper, DALL.E 3, Palm 2, Claude 2, Llama 2, Mistral, Zephyr, Orca 2, Gemini Pro, Mixtral 8x7b
•	Vector DB’s Pinecone, Qdrant, Chroma, MongoDB Atlas, Supabase

member_experience_collection.title: Lead Architect
member_experience_collection.description:
•	The main programme objective was to consolidate all data across the group, automate and use ML/AI to turn Capita into a data driven enterprise. 
•	I designed and lead the Build of a Secure, GDPR Compliant Data Platform. All data encrypted (in motion & at rest).
•	My design brought Realtime, Multi-Modal, Multi-Tennant, fully Automated & Cloud Agnostic Data capability to the organisation.
•	My design utilised both Azure & GCP 
•	My design relied heavily on Access to data, logically controlled by RBAC/ABAC/PBAC at an attribute level and exposed data through Micro Services. All data attributes directly tied to JWT Claims. 
•	I successfully got Data Engineers & Scientist to work cohesively in an integrated automated platform by using Databricks on Microsoft Azure for processing streaming events and running ML jobs.
•	The Platform used mainly Python for Ingestion (Airflow), Data Processing (PySpark) as well as Flask, Django frameworks.
•	I was central to bringing best practises, Agile processes.
•	I designed & Implemented a fully automated CI/CD pipelines, with Infrastructure as Code (Terraform & Helm) and Containerisation with Docker & Kubernetes.
•	I introduced the use of EDA Architecture concept, DAG’s, Event Sourcing & CQRS Patterns.
•	As Lead Architect I was also involved in designing other integration and platforms for many other Capita internal & external clients.
•	I implemented successful Blockchain Identity, Chatbots & an AI Candidate Vetting PoC.
•	As Lead Architect I worked on a many Business and Government Proposal & Bids.

member_experience_collection.title: Senior Enterprise Architect
member_experience_collection.description:
•	Produced HLD, LLD for transitioning multiple government departments to a multi-tenanted Hadoop big data platform using Hortonworks, HBase, Kafka, Elasticsearch.
•	I first had to consolidate disparate data models into a single canonical POLE model. 
•	I then designed & demonstrated how tenants can store and share data in a multi-tenanted platform with RBAC using claims embedded in the data.
•	Security is paramount, encryption at rest and in motion for everything was a crucial requirement for success. Kerberos was used for securing distributed components, encrypted disks, encrypted data, HTTPS, TLS, SSL & Hashing. 
•	I designed and implemented automated IAM, AD replication, KMS (KeyCloak) on HSM (Utimaco)
•	I worked extensively on the platform auditing, SIEM & SOC
•	I successfully produced & delivered PoCs to prove the architecture & drive the onboarding roadmap. 
•	I worked with very senior stakeholders, architects, and development teams to transition & migrate the home office from Crown hosting to AWS cloud using Linux & Windows VMs, Firehose, EC2, Kinesis, S3 & Redshift.

member_experience_collection.title: Co-Founder
member_experience_collection.description:
A cutting-edge platform that revolutionises the way we understand and interact with the spaces and entities around us. Using a network of sensors and actuators, we collect real-time data to train models that can make decisions at the edge without an internet connection. Our devices communicate through low energy wide area networks, ground-based gateways and low earth orbit satellites, some are equipped with blockchain identities that give them agency to perform transactions. SensationalGPT uses GPT-4 to chain other models so our devices can communicate and articulate their actions like never before. Experience the future of IoT and join us on the journey to transform the spaces around us.
